    "formula_md": "While linguistic conversion relies on dictionary mapping rather than a mathematical formula, the **VAT (Value Added Tax)** calculation uses standard percentage logic. \n\nWhen calculating the **Total Amount** including tax:\n\n$$ Total = Principal \\times \\left( 1 + \\frac{VAT\\_Rate}{100} \\right) $$\n\nWhere:\n* **Principal** is the input number.\n* **VAT_Rate** is the percentage tax.\n\nFor **Check Writing**, the fractional part is derived as:\n\n$$ Fraction = \\text{round}((Number - \\text{floor}(Number)) \\times 100) $$\n\nThe result is then formatted as \"XX/100\".",
